@node "Author" ""

 I was born in Salem Oregon, USA, and lived the first 18 years of
 my life there. Since then I have been doing a lot of traveling,
 both forigen and domestic.
 
 I took basic programing back in high school, where we used
 teletypes, and stored our programs on paper tape. Later I took
 a course in Fortran while going to college.
 
 I have done basic programing on the old C64 and C128. I also did
 a very little bit of assembly programing on the C128. As far as
 C goes on the Amiga, I am self taught. 
 
 So you can see that I don't have much in the way of an extensive
 programing background. But I manage to putter along. Although
 sometimes the simplest things can elude me for many days. If I
 can do it, anyone can do it.
 
 Hope you enjoy this program and find it useful.
    
@endnode

